<font color="#FF0000">HE'S BACK! OH WELL.</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jan 16 20:18:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
It would have been more peaceful if you had stayed away Dr. Spatz. But since you have returned, I must inform you I do not stand by for an attack of my personal integrity.<br><br>
You may not have felt you have done this. For starters, I never said I had to go through a guntlet of spitters. One was enough. It ws disturbing that when ever I neede to talk about what I had gone through to find resolution, I was visciously attacked verbally by those of you that &quot;protested the war&quot;.<br><br>
I find it strange that now you indicate you fought in the Six Day War in Sinai. I find that hard to believe. In fact I think you are lying. For if you did sit in a ditch weapon in hand you would have a better understanding of us who where in Vietnam.<br><br>
I never had to fight on the ground. My battles took place in the air aboard helicopters. No ditch to hide in. Just a vest to protect me. But I can certainly have compassion for the soldiers on the ground.<br><br>
I am glad you are back though. Maybe then I can get rid of this anger I have for the self-righteous folks as yourself.<br><br>
Tanker --<br><br>
Don't think for a minute Dr. Spatz is plaiyng with a full deck. As an advisor, you did one hell of a job under the conditions. As others have stated, including myself, Dr Spatz does not like people to disagree with his viewpoints.<br><br>
As for Winker and his ideas about Somalia, our troops there only went after Aidid after the other warlords were rendered in effective. At no time during our stay ther did we even attempt to establish a puppet government.<br><br>
We did support that type of government in Vietnam. So to that regard we did learn a lesson from that time period.<br><br>
Seems to me these &quot;war protestors&quot; have a problem with world history and current events. I would certainly have been in favor of going into battle during a six day war or a war that lasted only 100 hours.<br><br>
At least then I would not have had to worry about making it back from the next day's missions.
